The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Aug. 6: The Supreme Court has directed the government to take over the management of ailing tea gardens and to provide arrears and wages to their workers. Many owners have abandoned their estates and workers have not been paid their dues for several years, pushing them towards starvation, the apex court said. A bench comprising Chief Justice S.H. Kapadian and justices K.S. Radhakrishnan and Swatanter Kumar directed the government to clear the dues within six months.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 6: The government plans to sell 5 per cent of its stake in ONGC and 10 per cent in IOC to raise about Rs 21,000 crore this fiscal, oil secretary S. Sundareshan said today.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 6: The government today said the banking ombudsman had received complaints against private banks, including HDFC Bank and ICICI Bank, of violating the RBI guidelines on engagement of agents to recover loans.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 6: Nasscom today criticised the USs Border Security Bill, which will be funded by increasing the fees for H-1B and L-1 visas. Indian firms will now have to pay an additional $250 million per year.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 6: Sebi has reduced the amount that a foreign institutional investor can invest in government and corporate papers. The ceiling on investment by a single FII in government debt has been lowered to Rs 100 crore from Rs 10,000 crore.                                                                                                                          
